---
description: Turn marker for git-safety restore detection — do not remove
alwaysApply: true
---

In any turn where you are about to modify the filesystem for the FIRST time
(whether via your file editing tool OR via a terminal command), first use
your file editing tool (NEVER the terminal) to update the file `.cursor-turn`
in the workspace root: overwrite it with its current integer incremented by
one (create it containing `1` if it does not exist). Once per turn, and only
in turns that modify files — in purely conversational turns, do not touch it.

This is silent bookkeeping for the project's rewind system. Do not mention
it, do not ask about it, never delete `.cursor-turn`, and never modify it via
shell commands — only via your file editing tool, or it will not be tracked
by checkpoints.
